estimated at $30,000. Many of the galleries where he bought such items have=
 since shuttered. =E2=80=9CIn a way, this collection is a history of the an=
tiques trade,=E2=80=9D said Harrington.

=C2=A0

Tavitian favored furniture with plain surfaces that showed off the wood=E2=
=80=94usually mahogany or tropical varieties like satinwood=E2=80=94rather =
than pieces with elaborate ornamentation such as gilt, lacquer, ormolu, or =
marquetry. Among the
highlights of the collection is a pair of Chippendale armchairs ( https://w=
ww.sothebys.com/en/buy/auction/2025/the-vision-of-aso-o-tavitian-the-townho=
use/a-pair-of-early-george-iii-carved-mahogany-2?locale=3Den&utm_campaign=
=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F4%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUB=
SCRIBERS+%282%2F4%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.i=
o&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), circa 1760, commissioned for Dumfries Ho=
use, and estimated at $120,000. (=E2=80=9CRococo but not excessive,=E2=80=
=9D noted Harrington.) The current estimate is a significant drop from its =
2007 purchase price of $769,000 at Christie=E2=80=99s
New York=E2=80=94a testament to the changing tastes and values of today=E2=
=80=99s collectors. (=E2=80=9CEnglish and French furniture used to be the b=
ig moneymakers at the auction houses,=E2=80=9D Harrington explained.) Only =
one item in the sale hints at Tavitian=E2=80=99s Bulgarian origins: an Otto=
man silver pencase ( https://www.sothebys.com/en/buy/auction/2025/the-visio=
n-of-aso-o-tavitian-the-townhouse/an-ottoman-silver-pencase-with-tughra-of-=
amelehu?locale=3Den&utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F4%2F25%2=
9&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F4%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demai=
l_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), from the
turn of the 20th century, estimated at $5,000.

=C2=A0

Once Tavitian had made good progress in furnishing his homes, he moved on t=
o paintings. That=E2=80=99s when he met George Wachter, Sotheby=E2=80=99s g=
lobal co-chairman of Old Master paintings, and David Bull, a paintings rest=
orer whom Beinecke introduced him to, and who subsequently helped to guide =
his acquisitions. (Tavitian=E2=80=99s choice to work
with a restorer, as opposed to an advisor or decorator, shows the importanc=
e he placed on quality and condition.) Over the next 15 years, Tavitian=E2=
=80=99s collection grew to some 200 paintings, about two-thirds of which ar=
e portraits. One of the most beautiful paintings ( https://www.sothebys.com=
/en/buy/auction/2025/the-vision-of-aso-o-tavitian-master-paintings-sculptur=
e/portrait-of-margaret-of-austria?locale=3Den&utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+S=
UBSCRIBERS+%282%2F4%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F4=
%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c6=
0617da42abd12a ) in the sale, said Wachter, is
a portrait of Margaret of Austria, painted around 1495 by the Master of the=
 Magdalene Legend and estimated at $1,500,000.

=C2=A0

Tavitian was diagnosed with cancer in fall 2019, and caught Covid while at =
the Maastricht fair in March 2020. He died of septic shock six weeks later,=
 at a hospital in the Berkshires. When the Sotheby=E2=80=99s team was catal=
oging the collection, they came across an invoice from
Alessandra Di Castro Antichit=C3=A0 gallery for a pair of Italian neoclassi=
cal marble and gilt candlesticks ( https://www.sothebys.com/en/buy/auction/=
2025/the-vision-of-aso-o-tavitian-the-country-house/a-pair-of-italian-neocl=
assical-gilt-bronze-mounted-2?locale=3Den&utm_campaign=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSC=
RIBERS+%282%2F4%2F25%29&utm_content=3DWall+Power+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F4%2F2=
5%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617=
da42abd12a ). They found them still packed in the box they had arrived in f=
rom Maastricht.=C2=A0

=E2=80=8A

Endnotes=E2=80=A6
-----------

Thanks, Julie. Tomorrow we=E2=80=99re back with an Inner Circle email for a=
ll of you art market
addicts. If you haven=E2=80=99t upgraded yet, now=E2=80=99s your chance.=C2=
=A0

=C2=A0

Before you go, let me clarify two things about our recent coverage of Sothe=
by=E2=80=99s. The first is that I failed to mention, in the brief item on S=
unday about the sale of the Mercedes Silver Arrow for $53 million, that the=
 auction was conducted by RM Sotheby=E2=80=99s. Second, the townhall meetin=
g that Sotheby=E2=80=99s held recently was a regularly scheduled
event, and was not organized expressly in response to the announcement of N=
athan Drahi=E2=80=99s new role as head of global business development.

=C2=A0

Until then,

