for the collection, endowed a curatorial position to oversee it, and constr=
ucted a new wing to house it. =E2=80=9CHis collection was like family to hi=
m,=E2=80=9D said <strong>Candace Beinecke</strong>, Tavitian=E2=80=99s long=
time lawyer and friend, who also serves as the head of his foundation and a=
s co-chair of the board at the Met. =E2=80=9CHe adored every work and wante=
